  <refnamediv>
    <refname>lowdisc_destroy</refname>
    <refpurpose>  Destroy the current object and returns an updated object.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>this = lowdisc_destroy(this)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>this</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The current Random Number object. At output, the object is updated with the new settings.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
      This command allows to configure the state of the current object.
      It requires to take the current object both as an input
      and an output argument.
    </para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    In the following example, we create an 
    object and immediately destroys it. One finally clears the variable
    which holds the object.
    <programlisting role="example">
      rng = lowdisc_new();
      rng = lowdisc_destroy(rng);
      clear rng;
    </programlisting>
  </refsection>
